//! Witness marker `{{ row.rustType }}` — {{ row.description }}
//!
//! This is a **structure-only** authority label. It names `{{ row.witnessTitle }}`
//! as the canon a piece of evidence answers to. It does not check conformance.
//! Graduate to `wasm4pm` when the authority must be *verified*, not merely
//! *named*.
//!
//! ## What this IS
//!
//! A zero-sized uninhabited enum used as a `PhantomData` tag inside
//! [`crate::evidence::Evidence`], [`crate::admission::Admission`], and
//! [`crate::admission::Refusal`]. Its only observable content is the metadata
//! carried by [`crate::witness::Witness`] const items.
//!
//! ## What this is NOT
//!
//! Not a validator. Not a parser. Not a runtime value. Never put logic here.
//!
//! ## Graduation
//!
//! When a surface needs to actually verify conformance to
//! `{{ row.witnessTitle }}`, the witness travels into `wasm4pm` with its value.
//! Here it is only a label.
{% if row.paperReference %}
//!
//! ## Reference
//!
//! `{{ row.paperReference }}`
{% endif %}

